The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 799)

 This documentary takes a peek into the life of the ?king of swing?, Benny Goodman. It?s a story of how a man with a clarinet rose to become a cultural icon. There?s rare performance footage from the 20s to the 50s and appearances by greats such as Ella Fitzgerald, Louis Armstrong and Dizzy Gillespie.

 THE FILMS

 (Gorky Sadan, 6 pm, May 3 to 10) The Russian Consulate presents a bouquet of films capturing the fight against fascism. Mikhail Kalatozov?s Cranes are Flying is on Day One, to be followed by Grigory Chukhrai?s A Ballad of Soldier, Sergei Bondorchuk?s Fate of a Man, Stainislav Rostotsky?s At Dawn It Is Quiet Here and Mikhail Romm?s Ordinary Fascism.

 THE ACT

 (Max Mueller Bhavan, 6 pm, May 7)

 Conceived by Taran Khan, Swayam and Seagull Foundation for the Arts present this play on the friendship and social activism of three women ? Sultana Jafri, Zehra Mehdi and Shaukat Azmi ? in the turbulent 1940s.




